.

By @gym_worriors__
.
When you are designing your workout routine, it’s important for you to know which muscle groups to pair up in order to be effective and efficient in the gym.
_

I’m sure you’ve heard of a push, pull, legs split - in which one day is dedicated to working your “pushing”’muscles, another day spent towards your “pulling” muscles, and a final day spent on your legs.
_

The reason you would pair up a routine like this is because the muscles that are responsible for “pushing” or “pulling” essentially work in sync with one another. For instance, a bench press incorporates your pecs, shoulders, and triceps all in one movement. SO - since these muscles are all working together on a large portion of your lifts, it only make sense to pair them together when training. By doing so, your workouts will be more effective and efficient.
_
